<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<task id="R2-014" project="SprkChat Platform Enhancement R2">
  <metadata>
    <title>Document SPE Persistence Endpoint — Save Uploaded Documents to Matter's SPE Container</title>
    <status>pending</status>
    <phase>2</phase>
    <tags>bff-api, api</tags>
    <estimated-effort>medium</estimated-effort>
    <parallel-group>A</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>BFF API code implementation — creates a new Minimal API endpoint that integrates SpeFileStore upload with ChatHostContext resolution; FR-14 requirement</rigor-reason>
    <dependencies>[013]</dependencies>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Create a new BFF API endpoint that allows users to optionally persist a previously-uploaded chat
    document to the matter's SharePoint Embedded (SPE) container.

    **Endpoint**: `POST /api/ai/chat/sessions/{sessionId}/documents/{documentId}/persist`
    - Body: `{ "filename": "optional-override-name.pdf" }` (optional — defaults to original uploaded filename)

    **Processing**:
    1. Authorize request: verify caller owns `sessionId` via endpoint filter
    2. Retrieve the original binary content of the uploaded file from Redis:
       key `doc-upload:{sessionId}:{documentId}` — if not found, return `404 Not Found` ProblemDetails
    3. Resolve the matter's SPE container ID from `ChatHostContext` (which flows through the pipeline
       from the chat session's entity context)
    4. Call `SpeFileStore.UploadFileAsync(containerId, filename, content, contentType)` to persist
    5. Return `201 Created` with SPE file metadata:
       ```json
       {
         "speFileId": "...",
         "filename": "...",
         "url": "https://...",
         "sizeBytes": N,
         "uploadedAt": "..."
       }
       ```

    **Authorization**: Same `ChatSessionAuthorizationFilter` as the upload endpoint plus a check that
    the session's `ChatHostContext` has a valid SPE container ID.

    **Idempotency**: If the same `documentId` has already been persisted (check Redis for a
    `doc-persist:{sessionId}:{documentId}` marker), return `200 OK` with the existing SPE file
    metadata rather than uploading again.

    **Note**: This endpoint does NOT delete the session-scoped Redis entry — the uploaded document
    continues to be available for AI context until the session expires naturally (per NFR-06).
  </prompt>

  <role>Senior .NET developer with Azure AI and Minimal API expertise</role>

  <goal>
    A working `POST /api/ai/chat/sessions/{sessionId}/documents/{documentId}/persist` endpoint that
    retrieves an uploaded document from session-scoped Redis and uploads it to the matter's SPE container
    via `SpeFileStore`, returning the SPE file metadata. Saved documents appear in the matter's file
    browser (FR-14).
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="Project specification — FR-14 (optional SPE persist), design decision for session-scoped vs SPE storage">projects/ai-sprk-chat-platform-enhancement-r2/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="Project AI context — MUST rules, ChatHostContext flow, SpeFileStore pattern">projects/ai-sprk-chat-platform-enhancement-r2/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="SpeFileStore facade — upload method signatures and container resolution">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Storage/SpeFileStore.cs</file>
    <file purpose="Existing chat endpoints — authorization filter and ChatHostContext resolution patterns">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/ChatEndpoints.cs</file>
    <file purpose="Minimal API endpoint definition pattern">../.claude/patterns/api/endpoint-definition.md</file>
    <file purpose="Authorization endpoint filter pattern">../.claude/patterns/api/endpoint-filters.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-001">MUST use Minimal API pattern — no controllers</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-007">MUST use SpeFileStore.UploadFileAsync for all SPE writes — MUST NOT call Graph SDK directly</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-008">MUST apply authorization endpoint filter — session ownership + SPE container access verification</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">MUST flow `ChatHostContext` for SPE container ID resolution — the container ID is NOT hardcoded; it comes from the chat session's entity context</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-019">MUST return ProblemDetails for all error responses (404, 403, 500)</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-06">MUST NOT delete the session-scoped Redis upload on persist — session storage is separate from SPE persistence; both can coexist</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/ai-sprk-chat-platform-enhancement-r2/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/ai-sprk-chat-platform-enhancement-r2/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Storage/SpeFileStore.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/ChatEndpoints.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/ChatDocumentEndpoints.cs</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/api/endpoint-definition.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/api/endpoint-filters.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-007-spefilestore.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-008-endpoint-filters.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-013-ai-architecture.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern>SpeFileStore upload: `await _speFileStore.UploadFileAsync(containerId, filename, stream, contentType, cancellationToken)` — containerId comes from ChatHostContext.ContainerId</pattern>
      <pattern>Redis binary retrieval: stored bytes are the original file binary (not extracted text) — check the upload endpoint Redis storage format before reading; may need separate Redis key for the original binary vs extracted text</pattern>
      <pattern>Idempotency marker: `doc-persist:{sessionId}:{documentId}` key in Redis stores the SPE file metadata JSON; check for existence before re-uploading</pattern>
      <pattern>ChatHostContext resolution: look at how existing chat endpoints retrieve and use ChatHostContext — follow the same pattern (likely via IHttpContextAccessor or endpoint parameter)</pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      When a user uploads a document to SprkChat for analysis, the document lives temporarily in
      session-scoped Redis. After analysis, the user may want to save it to the matter's official
      file store (SPE container) so it appears in the AnalysisWorkspace file browser. This endpoint
      provides the "save to matter files" action.

      Key design decisions from the spec owner (clarification captured in spec.md):
      - Upload is session-scoped throwaway by default
      - Persist is an explicit user action ("save this to the matter files")
      - Both can coexist — session storage continues after persist

      The Redis binary storage note: Task R2-013 stores the EXTRACTED TEXT in Redis (for AI context).
      This task needs the ORIGINAL BINARY for SPE upload. Therefore R2-013 should also store the
      original binary with a separate key pattern, or this task needs to re-read the original upload.
      Check R2-013's implementation and document the binary storage key in `notes/013-document-upload-endpoint.md`.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      Strictly depends on Task R2-013 (upload endpoint must exist first; binary storage key must be
      established). Safe to run in parallel with all other Group A and Group B tasks (owns only the
      persist endpoint handler file). Task R2-042 (UI "save to matter files" action) in Phase 3 depends
      on this endpoint being available.
    </dependencies>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0">Read the completed `ChatDocumentEndpoints.cs` from R2-013 to understand how the original binary is stored in Redis (key pattern and data format)</step>
    <step order="1">If R2-013 did not store the original binary in Redis (only extracted text), add binary storage with key `doc-binary:{sessionId}:{documentId}` to R2-013's upload endpoint implementation</step>
    <step order="2">Read `SpeFileStore.cs` to confirm the `UploadFileAsync` method signature</step>
    <step order="3">Add the persist endpoint handler to `ChatDocumentEndpoints.cs` (same file as R2-013 for cohesion)</step>
    <step order="4">Implement Redis lookup for the original binary: retrieve `doc-binary:{sessionId}:{documentId}` — return 404 if not found</step>
    <step order="5">Resolve `ChatHostContext.ContainerId` from the session context — follow the existing pattern in `ChatEndpoints.cs`</step>
    <step order="6">Implement idempotency check: look for `doc-persist:{sessionId}:{documentId}` in Redis; if found, return 200 with stored metadata</step>
    <step order="7">Call `SpeFileStore.UploadFileAsync` with the binary content, filename, and container ID</step>
    <step order="8">Store SPE metadata in Redis with key `doc-persist:{sessionId}:{documentId}` and 4-hour TTL (same as session)</step>
    <step order="9">Return `201 Created` with `SpeFilePersistResponse` (speFileId, filename, url, sizeBytes, uploadedAt)</step>
    <step order="10">Apply authorization endpoint filter and rate limiting</step>
    <step order="11">Run `dotnet build` and verify no errors</step>
    <step order="12">Update TASK-INDEX.md: change task R2-014 status to completed (🔲 → ✅)</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool>dotnet</tool>
    <tool>git</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <artifact type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/ChatDocumentEndpoints.cs — persist endpoint added to the upload endpoint file</artifact>
    <artifact type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Models/Ai/Chat/SpeFilePersistResponse.cs — SPE file metadata response model</artifact>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`POST /api/ai/chat/sessions/{sessionId}/documents/{documentId}/persist` returns `201 Created` with SPE file metadata when document exists in Redis</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Calling the endpoint a second time with the same documentId returns `200 OK` with the same SPE file metadata (idempotent)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">If documentId does not exist in Redis, the endpoint returns `404 Not Found` with ProblemDetails body</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">The persisted file is retrievable via the SPE container and appears in AnalysisWorkspace file browser (manual verification)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">The session-scoped Redis key `doc-upload:{sessionId}:{documentId}` still exists after a successful persist (session storage not deleted)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Calling without valid session authorization returns `401 Unauthorized` from the endpoint filter</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`dotnet build` passes with no errors</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    The `SpeFileStore.UploadFileAsync` method requires a container ID. Verify that `ChatHostContext`
    carries the SPE container ID for the matter/entity in scope. If it does not, check whether
    `PlaybookChatContextProvider` resolves it — the container ID may need to be added to `ChatHostContext`
    as part of this task or a preceding one. This is a potential blocker — investigate early in step 0.

    The Word Online URL returned from this endpoint for .docx files would be of the form:
    `https://[tenant].sharepoint.com/_layouts/15/Doc.aspx?sourcedoc={fileId}` — this pattern is used
    by Task R2-022 (Open in Word endpoint) as well. Document the URL construction pattern in
    `notes/014-spe-persistence-urls.md` for R2-022 to reuse.
  </notes>

